==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unorganized
<hw>Un*or"gan*ized</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not organized;
being without organic structure; specifically <fld>(Biol.)</fld>, not
having the different tissues and organs characteristic of living
organisms, nor the power of growth and development; <as>as, the
<ex>unorganized</ex> ferments</as>. See the Note under <er>Ferment</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, 1.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unoriginated</ent>⟦br⟧
